  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You gain a +2&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Enhancement-Bonus\">enhancement bonus</a>&nbsp;on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/bluff\">Bluff</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/disguise\">Disguise</a>&nbsp;skill checks. This bonus increases by 1 for every 5&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/wizard\">wizard</a> levels you have, up to a maximum of +6 at 20th level. At 20th level, you gain the benefits of @Compendium[pf1.spells.8nrt26t37v7koqr8]{Misdirection}&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Will\">Will</a>&nbsp;DC = 20 + your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\">Intelligence</a> modifier) or @Compendium[pf1.spells.awia42zci8nufpfl]{Nondetection}&nbsp;permanently. At will as a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Standard-Actions\">standard action</a>, you can change which of the two spells is active, and each time you&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Activate-Magic-Item\">activate</a> @Compendium[pf1.spells.8nrt26t37v7koqr8]{Misdirection}, you can choose a new creature or object as the secondary object.</p>"
